{"type":"user","uuid":"ba59f5c6-5584-48e3-aa02-8dc34c1eb78d","session_id":"c7a56f37-52f8-4378-9a28-e0cf90afeea0","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4504cdda67273a5a1d8e1deccf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n# F-002 Code Review Report\n\n## 📋 Review Summary\n\n| Dimension | Status | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| **Spec Compliance** | ❌ FAIL | US-2 broken, US-4/US-5 partially broken |\n| **Plan Compliance** | ✅ PASS | Architecture matches plan.md |\n| **Code Quality** | ⚠️ WARN | Parser/validator design flaw |\n| **Security** | ✅ PASS | No security issues found |\n| **Test Coverage** | ⚠️ WARN | Tests pass but don't catch bug |\n| **Consistency** | ✅ PASS | Consistent code style |\n\n---\n\n## 🚨 CRITICAL Findings (Must Fix)\n\n### F002-CRIT-001: Parser Incorrectly Treats Positional Arguments as Subcommands\n\n**File**: `src/bot/commands/parser.js`, lines 76-79\n\n**Severity**: CRITICAL\n\n**Description**: The parser always treats the first non-option token as a subcommand, regardless of whether the command has subcommands defined.\n\n**Evidence**:\n```javascript\n// parser.js lines 76-79\n} else if (subcommand === undefined && !token.startsWith('-') && args.length === 0) {\n  // First non-option token is subcommand if it looks like one\n  // This will be validated by the registry\n  subcommand = token.toLowerCase();\n}\n```\n\n**Impact**:\n- `/bugfix session-123` → `subcommand: \"session-123\"`, `args: []` → **Validation fails**\n- `/logs my-feature` → `subcommand: \"my-feature\"`, `args: []` → **Target ignored**\n- `/stop my-feature` → `subcommand: \"my-feature\"`, `args: []` → **Target ignored**\n\n**Affected User Stories**:\n- US-2 (Bugfix Command): **COMPLETELY BROKEN**\n- US-4 (Logs Query): Target parameter ignored\n- US-5 (Stop Pipeline): Target parameter ignored\n\n**Fix Suggestion**:\n```javascript\n// Option 1: Parser should receive command metadata to know if command has subcommands\n// Option 2: Store first positional arg in args array, let validator map based on meta\n// Option 3: Validator should check parsed.subcommand as fallback for positional params\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ HIGH Findings\n\n### F002-HIGH-001: Validator Doesn't Map Positional Arguments\n\n**File**: `src/bot/commands/validator.js`, lines 102-115\n\n**Severity**: HIGH\n\n**Description**: The `getParamValue` function only checks `parsed.options`, not positional arguments stored in `subcommand` field.\n\n**Evidence**:\n```javascript\n// validator.js lines 102-115\nfunction getParamValue(parsed, paramName) {\n  // Check options first\n  if (parsed.options[paramName] !== undefined) {\n    return parsed.options[paramName];\n  }\n  // Check positional args (first arg maps to first positional param)\n  const positionalIndex = 0;\n  if (parsed.args[positionalIndex] !== undefined) {\n    // We need a smarter mapping - for now, use named params\n  }\n  return undefined;  // Never checks parsed.subcommand!\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📊 MEDIUM Findings\n\n### F002-MED-001: Duplicate Status Formatting Logic\n\n**File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` (line 173) and `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` (line 48)\n\n**Severity**: MEDIUM\n\n**Description**: Both files have nearly identical `formatStatusOutput` functions.\n\n**Fix**: Extract to shared utility module.\n\n---\n\n## 📝 LOW Findings\n\n### F002-LOW-001: Integration Tests Timeout\n\n**File**: `tests/integration/f002-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n\n**Description**: The comprehensive user stories integration tests timeout and don't complete.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Spec Compliance Matrix\n\n| User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Status | Evidence |\n|------------|---------------------|--------|----------|\n| **US-1** | `/pipeline run/status/logs/stop` | ✅ PASS | Tested successfully |\n| **US-1** | `/planner` behavior | ✅ PASS | `type=planner` set correctly |\n| **US-2** | `/bugfix <target>` starts bugfix pipeline | ❌ FAIL | Returns validation error |\n| **US-2** | Missing target shows usage | ✅ PASS | Works correctly |\n| **US-3** | `/status` shows pipelines | ✅ PASS | Works correctly |\n| **US-3** | No pipelines shows message | ✅ PASS | Shows \"当前没有运行中的管道\" |\n| **US-4** | `/logs` shows logs | ✅ PASS | Works correctly |\n| **US-4** | `/logs <target>` shows specific logs | ❌ FAIL | Target ignored |\n| **US-4** | Logs >= 4000 chars sent as file | ✅ PASS | Threshold implemented |\n| **US-5** | `/stop` stops pipeline | ✅ PASS | Works correctly |\n| **US-5** | `/stop <target>` stops specific pipeline | ❌ FAIL | Target ignored |\n| **US-6** | Error messages have suggestions | ✅ PASS | formatError provides suggestions |\n| **US-7** | All commands require auth | ✅ PASS | All `requiresAuth: true` |\n| **US-7** | Unauthorized message safe | ✅ PASS | No sensitive info exposed |\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Test Results\n\n| Test Suite | Passed | Failed | Status |\n|------------|--------|--------|--------|\n| parser.test.js | 18 | 0 | ✅ |\n| registry.test.js | 14 | 0 | ✅ |\n| validator.test.js | 14 | 0 | ✅ |\n| formatter.test.js | 10 | 0 | ✅ |\n| handlers.test.js | 14 | 0 | ✅ |\n| f002-command-router.integration.test.js | 6 | 0 | ✅ |\n| f002-user-stories.integration.test.js | - | - | ⏱️ Timeout |\n\n**Total Unit Tests**: 76 passed, 0 failed\n\n**Note**: Tests pass but don't catch the parser bug because they only check that commands are \"handled\" (returns true), not that they succeed.\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Verdict\n\n# ❌ NEEDS_FIXES\n\n**Reason**: CRITICAL spec compliance failure for US-2 (Bugfix Command). The `/bugfix <target>` command is completely non-functional.\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Required Actions Before Pass\n\n1. **Fix parser.js**: Don't treat all first tokens as subcommands - consider command metadata\n2. **Fix validator.js**: Map positional arguments correctly (consider `parsed.subcommand` as fallback)\n3. **Add integration tests**: That verify command success, not just \"handled\"\n4. **Re-run**: `prizmkit.code-review` after fixes\n\n---\n\n**Reviewer**: Reviewer Agent  \n**Feature**: F-002 Telegram Pipeline Command Router  \n**Date**: 2026-03-12  \n**Status**: NEEDS_FIXES → Return to Dev\n\n[Agent ID: agent-440b17be]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4504cdda67273a5a1d8e1deccf","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:21.235Z","_requestId":"33c1fe9f6f094d499ac61721329a98f3"}
