{"type":"user","uuid":"74d83791-6881-4df1-b45a-145892daf854","session_id":"c7a56f37-52f8-4378-9a28-e0cf90afeea0","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4fcb751d1019de4d681674715b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-dev\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated module implementer (multi-instance). Follows prizmkit.implement workflow with TDD, marks tasks [x] in tasks.md, works within assigned Git worktrees. Use when implementing specific feature modules.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-implement, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Dev Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的模块实现者。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"建筑工人\"——严格按图纸施工，使用 PrizmKit 的 implement 工作流作为执行引擎，专注于：\n  14→- 按照 tasks.md 和 plan.md 中的接口设计逐任务实现功能模块\n  15→- 遵循 TDD 方式开发（测试先行）\n  16→- 完成后立即标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`\n  17→- 产出代码和单元测试\n  18→\n  19→### 项目上下文\n  20→\n  21→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。实现前先读 `root.prizm` 了解规则和已知陷阱（TRAPS），修改某模块时读该模块的文档。\n  22→\n  23→### 制品路径\n  24→\n  25→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  26→|------|------|\n  27→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  28→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  29→\n  30→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  31→\n  32→1. 按照分配的任务和 plan.md 中的接口设计实现功能模块\n  33→2. 遵循 TDD 方式：先写测试，再实现，再验证\n  34→3. 产出的代码必须通过本模块的单元测试\n  35→4. 发现接口设计歧义时，立即通过 Coordinator 上报 PM（不自行假设）\n  36→5. 遵循 `prizmkit.implement` 工作流：读取 tasks.md + plan.md + spec.md，逐任务实现\n  37→6. 每个任务完成后**立即**标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`（不批量标记）\n  38→7. 实现前读取 `.prizm-docs/` TRAPS 段避免已知陷阱\n  39→8. 检查点任务须验证构建通过和测试通过后才能继续下一阶段\n  40→9. 顺序任务按序执行，失败则停止；并行 `[P]` 任务可继续\n  41→10. 新建子模块时，生成对应的 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  42→\n  43→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  44→\n  45→- 不修改 plan.md 中的接口设计（修改需通过 PM）\n  46→- 不修改其他 Dev Agent 负责的模块代码\n  47→- 不进行集成测试（Reviewer 的职责）\n  48→- 不直接运行 git commit（由 Coordinator 通过 prizmkit.committer 统一提交）\n  49→- 不修改 `.prizmkit/specs/` 中除 `tasks.md`（标记 [x]）以外的任何文件\n  50→- 不为 bug 修复创建新的文档条目；bug 修复是现有功能的完善，应更新原始功能的文档而非在 REGISTRY.md 中创建新条目\n  51→\n  52→### 行为规则\n  53→\n  54→```\n  55→DEV-01: 实现必须严格符合 plan.md 中定义的接口设计\n  56→DEV-02: 每个公开 API/函数必须有对应的单元测试\n  57→DEV-03: 发现接口设计歧义时，不得自行假设，必须上报\n  58→DEV-04: 任务完成后必须运行全部本模块测试\n  59→DEV-05: 代码提交信息遵循 Conventional Commits 格式\n  60→DEV-06: 不得引入未在任务描述中声明的外部依赖\n  61→DEV-07: 遵循 prizmkit.implement 工作流\n  62→DEV-08: 每个任务完成后立即标记 tasks.md [x]\n  63→DEV-09: TDD：先写测试 → 再实现 → 再验证\n  64→DEV-10: 实现每个模块前必须读取 .prizm-docs/ TRAPS 段\n  65→DEV-11: 检查点任务必须验证构建通过和测试通过\n  66→DEV-12: 新建子模块时生成 L2 .prizm-docs/ 文档\n  67→```\n  68→\n  69→### 工作流程\n  70→\n  71→1. 接收任务分配\n  72→2. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` 和相关模块文档\n  73→3. 读取 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` 中的 `tasks.md`、`plan.md`、`spec.md`\n  74→4. 对每个分配的任务，按 tasks.md 顺序执行：\n  75→   a. 读取目标文件模块的文档（检查 TRAPS 和 DECISIONS）\n  76→   b. TDD：基于验收标准编写测试 → 实现功能代码 → 运行测试验证\n  77→   c. 在 tasks.md 中标记该任务为 `[x]`\n  78→   d. 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 给 Coordinator\n  79→5. 如遇检查点任务，验证构建通过和测试通过后才继续\n  80→6. 遇到接口设计歧义，发送 ESCALATION（不自行假设）\n  81→7. 如新建了子模块，生成对应 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  82→8. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n  83→\n  84→### 异常处理\n  85→\n  86→| 场景 | 策略 |\n  87→|------|------|\n  88→| 接口设计歧义 | 标记 BLOCKED → ESCALATION → 等待 PM 裁定 |\n  89→| 单元测试失败 | 最多重试修复 3 次 → 仍失败则 ISSUE_REPORT |\n  90→| 外部依赖不可用 | 使用 Mock → 标注说明 |\n  91→| 任务超出预估 | ESCALATION → 建议 PM 拆分任务 |\n  92→\n  93→### 通信规则\n  94→\n  95→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n  96→- 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 汇报每个子任务完成\n  97→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 标志所有任务完成\n  98→- 发送 ESCALATION 上报接口歧义或任务阻塞\n  99→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 100→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4f9e54d751a312093867919dbc","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:39.370Z","_requestId":"33c1fe9f6f094d499ac61721329a98f3"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"28f168db-88ea-4402-aa45-a2bd0c5f5540","session_id":"c7a56f37-52f8-4378-9a28-e0cf90afeea0","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4fcdd2418066069e1935c459f1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n   2→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n   3→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n   4→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n   5→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n   6→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n   7→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n   8→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n   9→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n  10→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n  11→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n  12→\n  13→MODULE_INDEX:\n  14→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n  15→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n  16→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n  17→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n  18→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n  19→\n  20→LOAD_RULES:\n  21→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n  22→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n  23→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n  24→\n  25→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n  26→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n  27→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n  28→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4f9e54d751a312093867919dbc","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:39.370Z","_requestId":"33c1fe9f6f094d499ac61721329a98f3"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"85a37c63-2aef-42d5-b902-7ad4bf55d5ce","session_id":"c7a56f37-52f8-4378-9a28-e0cf90afeea0","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4fcfb4dc62dd3cde8e5d39e041","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Command Parser\n   3→ * Parses Telegram message text into structured ParsedCommand object.\n   4→ */\n   5→\n   6→/**\n   7→ * @typedef {Object} ParsedCommand\n   8→ * @property {string} command - The command name (e.g., \"pipeline\")\n   9→ * @property {string} [subcommand] - Optional subcommand (e.g., \"run\")\n  10→ * @property {string[]} args - Positional arguments\n  11→ * @property {Record<string, string>} options - Key-value options (--key=value)\n  12→ * @property {string} raw - Original message text\n  13→ */\n  14→\n  15→/**\n  16→ * Parse Telegram message text into a structured command object.\n  17→ * @param {string} text - The message text to parse\n  18→ * @param {Object} [aliasMap={}] - Map of aliases to command names\n  19→ * @returns {ParsedCommand | null} Parsed command or null if not a command\n  20→ */\n  21→export function parseCommand(text, aliasMap = {}) {\n  22→  if (!text || typeof text !== 'string') {\n  23→    return null;\n  24→  }\n  25→\n  26→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n  27→\n  28→  // Must start with /\n  29→  if (!trimmed.startsWith('/')) {\n  30→    return null;\n  31→  }\n  32→\n  33→  // Extract command (first token after /)\n  34→  const tokens = trimmed.slice(1).split(/\\s+/);\n  35→  if (tokens.length === 0 || !tokens[0]) {\n  36→    return null;\n  37→  }\n  38→\n  39→  let command = tokens[0].toLowerCase();\n  40→  const rest = tokens.slice(1);\n  41→\n  42→  // Handle @bot suffix (e.g., /command@mybot)\n  43→  const atIndex = command.indexOf('@');\n  44→  if (atIndex !== -1) {\n  45→    command = command.slice(0, atIndex);\n  46→  }\n  47→\n  48→  // Apply alias mapping\n  49→  if (aliasMap[command]) {\n  50→    command = aliasMap[command];\n  51→  }\n  52→\n  53→  const args = [];\n  54→  const options = {};\n  55→  let subcommand = undefined;\n  56→\n  57→  for (const token of rest) {\n  58→    // Parse --key=value options\n  59→    if (token.startsWith('--')) {\n  60→      const optionText = token.slice(2);\n  61→      const eqIndex = optionText.indexOf('=');\n  62→      if (eqIndex !== -1) {\n  63→        const key = optionText.slice(0, eqIndex).toLowerCase();\n  64→        const value = optionText.slice(eqIndex + 1);\n  65→        options[key] = value;\n  66→      } else {\n  67→        // Boolean flag --flag\n  68→        options[optionText.toLowerCase()] = 'true';\n  69→      }\n  70→    } else if (token.includes('=')) {\n  71→      // Parse key=value (without --)\n  72→      const eqIndex = token.indexOf('=');\n  73→      const key = token.slice(0, eqIndex).toLowerCase();\n  74→      const value = token.slice(eqIndex + 1);\n  75→      options[key] = value;\n  76→    } else if (subcommand === undefined && !token.startsWith('-') && args.length === 0) {\n  77→      // First non-option token is subcommand if it looks like one\n  78→      // This will be validated by the registry\n  79→      subcommand = token.toLowerCase();\n  80→    } else {\n  81→      // Positional argument\n  82→      args.push(token);\n  83→    }\n  84→  }\n  85→\n  86→  return {\n  87→    command,\n  88→    subcommand,\n  89→    args,\n  90→    options,\n  91→    raw: text\n  92→  };\n  93→}\n  94→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4f9e54d751a312093867919dbc","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:39.371Z","_requestId":"33c1fe9f6f094d499ac61721329a98f3"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"dd4b8546-cf7e-40f1-9715-8e3ecd0b414e","session_id":"c7a56f37-52f8-4378-9a28-e0cf90afeea0","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde4fd155d5aa629788b1fb595a61","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Command Validator\n   3→ * Validates command parameters and generates error messages.\n   4→ */\n   5→\n   6→/**\n   7→ * @typedef {Object} ValidationError\n   8→ * @property {string} param - Parameter name\n   9→ * @property {string} message - Error message\n  10→ * @property {string} [suggestion] - Correction suggestion\n  11→ */\n  12→\n  13→/**\n  14→ * @typedef {Object} ValidationResult\n  15→ * @property {boolean} valid - Whether validation passed\n  16→ * @property {ValidationError[]} errors - Validation errors\n  17→ * @property {Record<string, *>} [normalized] - Normalized parameters\n  18→ */\n  19→\n  20→/**\n  21→ * @typedef {import('./parser.js').ParsedCommand} ParsedCommand\n  22→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').CommandMeta} CommandMeta\n  23→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').ParamMeta} ParamMeta\n  24→ * @typedef {import('./registry.js').SubcommandMeta} SubcommandMeta\n  25→ */\n  26→\n  27→/**\n  28→ * Validate a parsed command against its metadata.\n  29→ * @param {ParsedCommand} parsed - Parsed command\n  30→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n  31→ * @returns {ValidationResult} Validation result\n  32→ */\n  33→export function validateCommand(parsed, meta) {\n  34→  const errors = [];\n  35→  const normalized = { ...parsed.options };\n  36→\n  37→  // Validate subcommand if command has subcommands\n  38→  if (meta.subcommands?.length) {\n  39→    const validSubcommands = meta.subcommands.map((s) => s.name);\n  40→    if (parsed.subcommand && !validSubcommands.includes(parsed.subcommand)) {\n  41→      errors.push({\n  42→        param: 'subcommand',\n  43→        message: `未知子命令 '${parsed.subcommand}'`,\n  44→        suggestion: `可用子命令: ${validSubcommands.join(', ')}`\n  45→      });\n  46→    }\n  47→  }\n  48→\n  49→  // Get applicable params\n  50→  const params = getParamsForSubcommand(meta, parsed.subcommand);\n  51→\n  52→  // Validate parameters\n  53→  for (const param of params) {\n  54→    const value = getParamValue(parsed, param.name);\n  55→    const result = validateParam(param, value);\n  56→\n  57→    if (!result.valid) {\n  58→      errors.push(result.error);\n  59→    } else if (result.value !== undefined) {\n  60→      normalized[param.name] = result.value;\n  61→    }\n  62→  }\n  63→\n  64→  // Add positional args to normalized\n  65→  if (parsed.args.length > 0) {\n  66→    normalized._args = parsed.args;\n  67→  }\n  68→\n  69→  return {\n  70→    valid: errors.length === 0,\n  71→    errors,\n  72→    normalized: errors.length === 0 ? normalized : undefined\n  73→  };\n  74→}\n  75→\n  76→/**\n  77→ * Get parameters applicable to a subcommand.\n  78→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n  79→ * @param {string|undefined} subcommand - Subcommand name\n  80→ * @returns {ParamMeta[]} Parameters\n  81→ */\n  82→function getParamsForSubcommand(meta, subcommand) {\n  83→  const params = [...(meta.params || [])];\n  84→\n  85→  // Add subcommand-specific params\n  86→  if (subcommand && meta.subcommands) {\n  87→    const subMeta = meta.subcommands.find((s) => s.name === subcommand);\n  88→    if (subMeta?.params) {\n  89→      params.push(...subMeta.params);\n  90→    }\n  91→  }\n  92→\n  93→  return params;\n  94→}\n  95→\n  96→/**\n  97→ * Get parameter value from parsed command.\n  98→ * @param {ParsedCommand} parsed - Parsed command\n  99→ * @param {string} paramName - Parameter name\n 100→ * @returns {string|undefined} Parameter value\n 101→ */\n 102→function getParamValue(parsed, paramName) {\n 103→  // Check options first\n 104→  if (parsed.options[paramName] !== undefined) {\n 105→    return parsed.options[paramName];\n 106→  }\n 107→\n 108→  // Check positional args (first arg maps to first positional param)\n 109→  const positionalIndex = 0; // Simplified: first positional param\n 110→  if (parsed.args[positionalIndex] !== undefined) {\n 111→    // We need a smarter mapping - for now, use named params\n 112→  }\n 113→\n 114→  return undefined;\n 115→}\n 116→\n 117→/**\n 118→ * Validate a single parameter.\n 119→ * @param {ParamMeta} param - Parameter metadata\n 120→ * @param {string|undefined} value - Parameter value\n 121→ * @returns {{valid: boolean, error?: ValidationError, value?: *}}\n 122→ */\n 123→function validateParam(param, value) {\n 124→  // Check required\n 125→  if (param.required && (value === undefined || value === '')) {\n 126→    return {\n 127→      valid: false,\n 128→      error: {\n 129→        param: param.name,\n 130→        message: `缺少参数 '${param.name}'`,\n 131→        suggestion: `请提供 ${param.name} 参数`\n 132→      }\n 133→    };\n 134→  }\n 135→\n 136→  // If not provided and has default, use default\n 137→  if (value === undefined && param.default !== undefined) {\n 138→    return { valid: true, value: param.default };\n 139→  }\n 140→\n 141→  // If not provided and not required, OK\n 142→  if (value === undefined) {\n 143→    return { valid: true };\n 144→  }\n 145→\n 146→  // Type validation\n 147→  if (param.type === 'number') {\n 148→    const num = Number(value);\n 149→    if (Number.isNaN(num)) {\n 150→      return {\n 151→        valid: false,\n 152→        error: {\n 153→          param: param.name,\n 154→          message: `参数 '${param.name}' 必须是数字`,\n 155→          suggestion: `请输入有效的数字`\n 156→        }\n 157→      };\n 158→    }\n 159→    return { valid: true, value: num };\n 160→  }\n 161→\n 162→  // Enum validation\n 163→  if (param.type === 'enum' && param.enum?.length) {\n 164→    if (!param.enum.includes(value)) {\n 165→      return {\n 166→        valid: false,\n 167→        error: {\n 168→          param: param.name,\n 169→          message: `参数 '${param.name}' 值无效: ${value}`,\n 170→          suggestion: `可选值: ${param.enum.join(', ')}`\n 171→        }\n 172→      };\n 173→    }\n 174→  }\n 175→\n 176→  return { valid: true, value };\n 177→}\n 178→\n 179→/**\n 180→ * Validate that a subcommand is valid for a command.\n 181→ * @param {string} subcommand - Subcommand name\n 182→ * @param {SubcommandMeta[]} subcommands - Available subcommands\n 183→ * @returns {{valid: boolean, error?: ValidationError}}\n 184→ */\n 185→export function validateSubcommand(subcommand, subcommands) {\n 186→  if (!subcommand) {\n 187→    return { valid: true };\n 188→  }\n 189→\n 190→  const validNames = (subcommands || []).map((s) => s.name);\n 191→  if (validNames.length === 0) {\n 192→    return { valid: true };\n 193→  }\n 194→\n 195→  if (!validNames.includes(subcommand)) {\n 196→    return {\n 197→      valid: false,\n 198→      error: {\n 199→        param: 'subcommand',\n 200→        message: `未知子命令 '${subcommand}'`,\n 201→        suggestion: `可用子命令: ${validNames.join(', ')}`\n 202→      }\n 203→    };\n 204→  }\n 205→\n 206→  return { valid: true };\n 207→}\n 208→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde4f9e54d751a312093867919dbc","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:11:39.371Z","_requestId":"33c1fe9f6f094d499ac61721329a98f3"}
